Merge pull request #67 from r4ngy4l/patch-1

Update restrictions in documentation

Update restrictions in documentation

addtoblock and with_data tags must not be used in a template included with only option.
Inside such a template the original context, where sekizai data is stored, is not accessible.
release 0.10.0
dropped 2.6 support, updated docs for dj 1.10
Updating travis to run build on Django 1.10
Updated docstring for test helper function.
Moved code for changing template debug in tests to its own method. Also should play better with older django versions.
Adding django 1.10 support to sekizai. Fixed tests to work with changes.

Merge pull request #62 from adamchainz/readthedocs.io

Convert readthedocs link for their .org -> .io migration for hosted projects

Convert readthedocs link for their .org -> .io migration for hosted projects

As per [their blog post of the 27th April](https://blog.readthedocs.com/securing-subdomains/) ‘Securing subdomains’:

> Starting today, Read the Docs will start hosting projects from subdomains on the domain readthedocs.io, instead of on readthedocs.org. This change addresses some security concerns around site cookies while hosting user generated data on the same domain as our dashboard.
